President Obama announced his intent to nominate and appoint several individuals to key Administration posts. The nominations include Ann Calvaresi Barr for Inspector General of the United States Agency for International Development, Julius Lloyd Horwich for Assistant Secretary for Legislative and Congressional Affairs in the Department of Education, and Greg Nadeau for Administrator of the Federal Highway Administration in the Department of Transportation. The appointments include Elizabeth H. Blackburn as a member of the President's Committee on the National Medal of Science, Xavier Briggs as a member of the Community Development Advisory Board, Jacob James Fitisemanu Jr. as a member of the President's Advisory Commission on Asian Americans and Pacific Islanders, Sanjita Pradhan as a member of the President's Advisory Commission on Asian Americans and Pacific Islanders, Paul Y. Watanabe as a member of the President's Advisory Commission on Asian Americans and Pacific Islanders, Peter V. Berns as a member of the President's Committee for People with Intellectual Disabilities, James T. Brett as a member of the President's Committee for People with Intellectual Disabilities, Kenneth Capone as a member of the President's Committee for People with Intellectual Disabilities, Zachary W. Holler as a member of the President's Committee for People with Intellectual Disabilities, Deborah M. Spitalnik as a member of the President's Committee for People with Intellectual Disabilities, and Elizabeth Weintraub as a member of the President's Committee for People with Intellectual Disabilities.